Ecology.Relationships:
Sea gulls were [[favored animal]]s of the [[Untheric pantheon|Untheric deity]] [[Ramman]], as well as the [[Faerûnian pantheon|Faerûnian powers]] [[Shaundakul]] and [[Valkur]].{{Cite web enhancement/Deity Do's and Don'ts|14-15}} Shaundakul was known to send gulls to guide or aid his faithful. And Valkur [[specialty priest]]s, [[stormharbor]]s, often had a sea gull design embroidered on their outfits with gold thread in the belief that it would bring them good luck.

The inhabitants of the Paikai islands believed these birds to be representatives of the souls of the dead. They held an annual ceremony, called the [[Festival of Seagulls]], in which they would leave out plates of raw meat for them.

In the Shutters, one of the neighborhoods of Ravens Bluff's [[Ravens Bluff/Crow's End|Crow's End District]], impoverished children would often try to kill any sea gulls that swooped down by throwing sticks and stones at them. They would then bring the bird back to their homes to be made into food.

In the Great Glacier region, they were one of the many staple birds in the diet of [[Iulutiun]]s. And the inhabitants of [[Cragmyr]] would also supplement the [[chicken]]s they raised by [[sling]]ing down gulls.<ref name="drag200-p144>{{Cite dragon/200/Elminster's Notebook: Lord Kuldak Maurancz|144}}

Some aquatic [[ranger]]s were known to have gulls as [[animal companion]]s. [[Mage]]s that practiced [[Sea (province)|sea magic]] often had them as [[familiar]]s{{Cite dragon/235/Mage on Deck!|32}} and used them as targets for the [[spell]] ''[[animal messenger]]''.{{Cite dragon/220/Arcane Lore: Sea Magic|72}} Those [[summon]]ed by the spell ''[[find familiar]]'' typically had black feathers and were in the larger range of size.{{Cite dragon/84/A cast of strange familiars|14}}
